"},"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TMO":{"title":"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TMO","creator":"LinOnetwo","type":"text/vnd.tiddlywiki","text":"[[TMO|https://oscaf.sourceforge.net/tmo.html#tmo:taskReference]] refers to the Task Management Ontology. In general, it allows for the detailed and clear management of individual pending tasks. The TMO Ontology can be used to describe personal tasks of individuals, also known as to-do lists. It is based on RDF and NRL, the Nepomuk Representational Language and other Semantic Web ontologies.The corresponding field names and their values are listed below. Some of the fields have duplicated functions and can be freely selected.

<$json-editor-form filter="[[$:/TraitTag/TMO/Task]get[schema]]" tiddler="$:/temp/TMO-example" />

Note that some fields have been removed from the original TMO for the following reasons:

* SuperTask: this field is used to indicate the parent task of a task, but in TiddlyWiki this can be done by tagging the hierarchy.
* SubTask: this field is used to indicate the subtasks of the task, as above.
* Attachment: this field is used to indicate an attachment to a task, but in TiddlyWiki this should be accomplished by linking to the attachment tiddler in the note. All internal links should be treated as attachments.
* TaskPrivacyState: this field is used to indicate the privacy state of the task, but in TiddlyWiki this should be implemented by tagging with FileSystemPath.
* ContextThread: describes the context of the task, in TiddlyWiki this can be achieved by using the body of the tiddler.
* TaskName: describes the title of the task, in TiddlyWiki, this can be realized by the title field of the tiddler.
* IndexPosition: describes the ordering of the task in the hierarchy, in TiddlyWiki this can be done via the `list` field of the tiddler.
* SubTaskOrdering: describes the ordering of subtasks, as above.
* TaskId: describes the unique identifier of the task, but in TiddlyWiki this can be done with the `title` field of the tiddler.
* TaskReference: describes the other tasks that the current task references, being tmo:superTask (direct), tmo:dependencyMemberA (direct), tmo:dependencyMemberB (direct), tmo: transmissionTask (direct), tmo:taskSource (direct), etc. In TiddlyWiki, there is no usage of parent concepts for the time being, so it is sufficient to estimate the deletion of them and just use these children of it.
* InvolvedPersons: describes the participants of the task, which in Tiddlywiki can be accomplished by adding the person entry as a tag to the task entry."},"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/CalendarDefaultTag/Title":{"title":"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/CalendarDefaultTag/Title","text":"Calendar default tag"},"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/CalendarDefaultTag/Description":{"title":"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/CalendarDefaultTag/Description","text":"Auto added tag when adding task-related calendar entry. This overrides the global setting."},"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/DueDate/Title":{"title":"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/DueDate/Title","text":"Due Date"},"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/DueDate/Description":{"title":"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/DueDate/Description","text":"The date by which the task should be completed."},"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/AbilityCarrierInvolvement/Title":{"title":"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/AbilityCarrierInvolvement/Title","text":"Ability Carrier Involvement"},"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/AbilityCarrierInvolvement/Description":{"title":"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/AbilityCarrierInvolvement/Description","text":"Associates entities capable of action or involvement in tasks, modeled as 'AbilityCarriers.'"},"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/TaskGoal/Title":{"title":"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/TaskGoal/Title","text":"Task Goal"},"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/TaskGoal/Description":{"title":"$:/plugins/linonetwo/tmo/language/en-GB/TraitTag/TMO/Task/TaskGoal/Description","text":"The primary objective that the task aims to achieve."},"$:/plugins/linonetwo/t